                    <idno type="FIEY">414</idno>
                    <sex value="M" source="#bib1475-2">male</sex>
                    <death when="0433" syriaca-computed-start="0433-01-01" source="#bib1475-2">433</death>
                    <floruit when="0396" syriaca-computed-start="0396" source="#bib1475-2">396</floruit>
                    <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bib1475-2">Simeon est fete par les Syriaques occidentaux le rer ou le 2 octobre, le 4,
13 ou 18 janvier.
Nau, Notice, 8-18; BHO, 1120.
Palmer, Monk and Mason, sommaire 15 et passim.
BSO, II, 1030-31 (J.M. Fiey).</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1475">Simeon was known as the second founder of
          the monastery of Qartmin or <placeName ref=" http://syriaca.org/place/226">Mor
            Gabriel</placeName>. He was healed at a young age by Samuel of Qartmin, who also
          instructed him in monasticism. An angel led them to the place where they were to construct
          the monastery of Qartmin. He was the second abbot of Qartmin and blessed <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/26">Rabbula</persName> of Edessa.</note>
                    <note type="disambiguation">with <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/26">Rabbula</persName>
                    </note>
                    <event type="attestation" xml:id="attestation1475-1" source="#bib1475-2">
                        <p xml:lang="en">Shemʿun is commemorated in <title ref="http://syriaca.org/work/1064">Simeon of Qartmin (text)</title>.</p>
                    </event>
